File: Adam Catzavelos with members of the Seth Mazibuko Foundation. JOHANNESBURG - Adam Catzavelos has pleaded guilty to crimen injuria charge. He appeared at the Randburg Magistrates' Court on Thursday. His legal team says Catzavelos admits that the use of K-word is hurtful and that he did not intend to harm anyone. Catzavelos will be back in court on 13 February 2020 for mitigation and aggravation of sentence. READ: A moment of madness: Catzavelos on k-word rant Catzavelos came under fire after he filmed himself using the k-word while on holiday in Greece in August last year.